OL,6,FRichards, of Brownlow Close in
OL,7,FPortsmouth, appeared at Portsmouth
OL,8,FMagistrates Court on 26 July, charged
OL,9,Fwith 24 shoplifting offences which
OL,10,Ftook place between January and April.
OL,12,FRichards has been jailed for eight
OL,13,Fmonths.
OL,15,FHampshire & Isle of Wight
OL,16,FConstabulary's retail crime lead,
OL,17,FChief Inspector Marcus Cator, said:
OL,18,F"This sentence is just one result of
OL,19,Fan ongoing and dedicated focus on
OL,20,Ftargeting our most prolific offenders
OL,21,Fas effectively as possible.
